# APIs and events

- Preserve backward compatibility unless a breaking change is explicitly approved.
- Use stable machine-readable error codes.
- Pagination must have bounded page size.
- Mutating operations that may be retried should support idempotency.
- Do not expose internal stack traces or implementation details.
- Update OpenAPI/examples/tests together with behavior.
- Version events and use additive evolution.
- Consumers must be idempotent and tolerate duplicate delivery.
- Use dead-letter handling and observable retry behavior.
- Never put secrets or unnecessary sensitive data in events.
